## Animations — AnimateIn Only

```tsx
import { AnimateIn, AnimateInGroup } from "@nebutra/ui/components";

// Single entrance
<AnimateIn preset="emerge">          // blur+rise (default)
<AnimateIn preset="flow">            // slide from left
<AnimateIn preset="fade">
<AnimateIn preset="fadeUp">
<AnimateIn preset="scale">

// Scroll-triggered (landing page)
<AnimateIn preset="emerge" inView>

// Staggered list
<AnimateInGroup stagger="normal" className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  {items.map(item => <AnimateIn key={item.id} preset="fadeUp"><Card /></AnimateIn>)}
</AnimateInGroup>
```

**NEVER** use `motion.div` with hardcoded `initial`/`animate` values.

## Next.js 16 Patterns

```
proxy.ts (NOT middleware.ts)   — request interception, runs Node.js runtime
Server Components               — default; 'use client' only for browser APIs
Server Actions ('use server')   — for all mutations
Route Handlers                  — only for public APIs, webhooks, file uploads
async cookies() / headers()     — all request APIs are now async
'use cache'                     — Cache Components for ISR-like behavior
```

## API Gateway Patterns (Hono)

```typescript
// apps/api-gateway/src/routes/<domain>.ts
import { Hono } from "hono";
import { zValidator } from "@hono/zod-validator";
import { requirePermission } from "@nebutra/permissions";
import { getCurrentTenant } from "@nebutra/tenant";
import { NebutraError } from "@nebutra/errors";

const app = new Hono();

app.get("/api/v1/resource",
  requirePermission("read", "Resource"),
  async (c) => {
    const tenant = getCurrentTenant();
    const data = await db.resource.findMany({ where: { tenantId: tenant.tenantId } });
    return c.json({ data });
  }
);
```

## Permissions Reference

Scopes: `read`, `create`, `update`, `delete`, `manage`, `export`
Resources: `Project`, `Member`, `ApiKey`, `Billing`, `Webhook`, `Integration`, `Analytics`

Roles (descending authority): `OWNER` → `ADMIN` → `MEMBER` → `VIEWER`

```tsx
// Hono middleware
app.delete("/api/v1/projects/:id", requirePermission("delete", "Project"), handler);

// React gate
import { Can } from "@nebutra/permissions/react";
<Can action="delete" resource="Project" subject={project}>
  <DeleteButton />
</Can>
```

